Chapter: Tokens

  A token is a lexical element produced by the lexer. It carries a kind,
  the original source text, and position information.

    Token = record {
      kind : TokenKind,
      text : Text,
      offset : Integer,
      line : Integer,
      column : Integer
    }

  We can ask for the length of a token's text:

    token-length : Token -> Integer
    token-length (t) = text-length t.text
